Governor Nyesom Wike of Rivers State Thursday announced the suspension of 12 local government chairmen in the state. Their suspension was announced in a terse statement in Port Harcourt, by Special Assistant on Electronic Media, Mr. Simeon Nwakaudu. According to the statement, the suspended Council Chairmen are those of Okrika; Emohua; Abua/Odual; Degema; Khana and Gokana LGAs. Others are Ahoada East; Ikwerre; Eleme; Andoni; Omuma; and Ogu/Bolo LGAs. Nwakaudu added that the affected council chairmen were suspended for failure to participate in an official function.